@NODE CONTENTS
                                  CONTENTS

This software package consists of the following files:

ModPlayer			- the program itself
ModPlayer.info			- it`s icon

ModPlayer.iff			- the documentation-picture
ModPlayer.iff.info		- it`s icon

ModPlayer.doc			- the english documentation
ModPlayer.doc.info		- it`s icon

ModPlayer_english.guide		- this hypertext for AmigaGuide
ModPlayer_english.guide.info	- it`s icon

Modplayer.font			- the font
Modplayer/6			- the font`s datafile

Commands/MPLoad			- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPStop			- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPPause		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPPlay			- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPForward		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPKillMod		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPPalNtsc		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPFilter		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPHide			- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPBackward		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPModInfo		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPEqualizer		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPExtend		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPProtect		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPLoadConfig		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPSaveConfig		- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPUp			- cli-remotecommand
Commands/MPDown			- cli-remotecommand

Sources/ModPlayerControl.s	- example source

@ENDNODE

=============================================================================
@NODE DESCRIPTION
                                 DESCRIPTION

     The ModPlayer is able to replay most of the Protrackermodules.

It requires  @{"Kickstart  2.04"  LINK COPYRIGHT}, @{"Workbench 2.0"
LINK COPYRIGHT} or better.

It`s possible to control it with the CLI-commands in the "Commands" directory.

The ModPlayer contains an embedded version id in CBM format which can be shown
using the Shell command VERSION of Workbench 2.0.

All program components are tested with Enforcer V37.28 and MungWall V37.55.

@ENDNODE

=============================================================================
@NODE USAGE
                                    USAGE

Start the ModPlayer from CLI or Workbench.
From the CLI, you have the following options:

 P	= PAL			- Set Pal-Speed
 N	= NTSC			- Set Ntsc-Speed
 F	= FILTER		- Enable Filter
 NF	= NOFILTER		- Disable Filter
 H	= HIDE			- Hide the Window
 NH	= NOHIDE		- Open the Window
 PR	= PROTECT		- Enable Protection to check the mod before
                                  playing
 NPR	= NOPROTECT		- Disable Protection
 VE	= VERTEQUALIZER		- Use vertical Equalizer
 HE	= HORIZEQUALIZER	- Use horizontal Equalizer
 PA	= PATH			- Define a default Path e.g: "ST-00:Modules"
 M	= MODULE		- Define a default Module e.g: "mod.dangerzone"
 PA	= PATTERN		- Define a default Pattern e.g: "mod.#?"

@ENDNODE

=============================================================================
@NODE FEATURES
                                  FEATURES

  - ProTrackerV2.3A replayroutine
  - Two different 4 channel equalizers
  - ASL-FileRequester
  - ModInfoPage
  - Scroller
  - Controlport
  - Trackdisplay
  - Hidemode
  - Errormessages
  - GUI-Cli-arguments 
  - Configfile "S:ModPlayer.cfg"
  - Loads a module automatically after start
  - Allocates the audiochannels
  - Uses CIA for interrupt
  - Switch for Pal/Ntsc speed

@ENDNODE

=============================================================================
@NODE SPECIAL
                                   SPECIAL

The ModPlayer has it`s own MessagePort named "ModPlayerControlPort".
It uses sigbit 31, the messagedata is just one longword, the message
will be replied! These are the commands:

  0	=	_NoCommand
  1	=	_Load
  2	=	_Stop
  3	=	_Pause
  4	=	_Play
  5	=	_Forward
  6	=	_KillMod
  7	=	_PalNtsc
  8	=	_Filter
  9	=	_Hide
 10	=	_Backward
 11	=	_ModInfo
 12	=	_Equalizer
 13	=	_Extend
 14	=	_Protect
 15	=	_LoadConfig
 16	=	_SaveConfig

 17	=	_Up
 18	=	_Down

 Check out the file: "ModPlayerControl.s" in the sources Directory.

@ENDNODE

=============================================================================
@NODE HISTORY
                                   HISTORY
V1.0> (not released)

  - noisetrackerv1.0 replay
  - small "Closewindow"
  - cli-usage

V2.04> only Kick 2.x (released beta version!)

  - replaced nt1.0 with protrackerv2.1b replayroutine.
  - added default module: mod.intuidef.
  - added ASL-Filerequester.
  - added a window with close, zoom, scroller, equalizer and controlbuttons.
  - added controlbuttons:
    - load.
    - stop.
    - pause.
    - play.
    - fast forward.
    - killmod (freemem).
    - pal/ntsc.
    - filter on/off.
    - open/close window.

V2.1>

  - .info file is now docfile!
  - changed sigbit to 31 and portname to ModPlayerControlPort.
  - created the ModPlayerControlWindow controls the ModPlayer over its msgport.
  - added the MPC in my first game Reversi.

V2.2>

  - fixed bug in the cli-usage.
  - replaced fastforward with next pattern.
  - changed default module name to: mod.default.
  - added the ModPlayerOpen-Close,which opens or closes the MP window.
  - added last pattern.
  - added the last pattern function to the MPCW.
  - added the trackdisplay.
  - added size of patternlist.
  - added current position in patternlist.
  - added current pattern number.
  - added a modinfopage behind the trackdisplay.
  - added Errormessages.
  - added cache auto on/off.
  - added the protection mode.
  - added a docfile.

V2.21 (22 Dec. 92)>

  - added a dragbar to the ModInfoPage.
  - changed some gadgetpositions.
  - removed the docfile from the .info file.

V3.07 (17 Apr. 93)>
  - totally recoded the ModPlayer.
  - replaced textprinter with a scroller.
  - replaced ProTrackerV2.1B with ProTrackerV2.3A replayroutine.
  - replaced VBI- with CIA-interrupt.
  - build own close, drag and upfrontgadget.
  - added switchable equalizer.
  - added extend gagdet with extension.
  - added configfile.
  - added some chars to the font.
  - added an audiocahnnel allocation.
  - added an iff-docpicture.
  - added amigaguide-docfile
  - redesigned the modinfopage.
  - changed equalizer draw-routines to avoid flicker.
  - redesigned CLI-argument parsing.


@ENDNODE

